The paper deals with coordination mechanisms and game theory in the context of scheduling on unrelated machines, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GT (Game Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of approximation ratios and potential function arguments also suggests a connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
